name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: The Florida Department of Health in Marion County would like to wish you and yours a Happy Thanksgiving on Thursday. We also remind you that our offices will be closed on Nov. 25 and 26. We will resume normal operations on Nov. 29. Have a great holiday!  https://t.co/zqdct3NImP

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: As Marion County residents prepare to celebrate Thanksgiving, our friends at Marion County Fire Rescue offer some helpful advice on staying safe for those who prefer to deep fry their turkeys.  https://t.co/AwHwo2egLI

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: A reminder: just because your bird looks done doesn't mean it is done. Don't let an undercooked turkey ruin your holiday.

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Today is the annual Great American Smokeout. Think about quitting smoking today. @tobaccofreefla can help you learn more about how to do that. Visit  https://t.co/JIK2RkG0Xb.  https://t.co/anU9T4H3Db

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Annually in Marion County injuries kill about 20 people age 19 or younger. At noon today, on #NationalInjuryPreventionDay, Dr @robinpetroze of @UFHealth offers advice on keeping kids safe with a free webinar. To sign up or learn more, go to  https://t.co/Hz6YP5FuF2. #BeInjuryFree

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Injury is the 3rd leading cause of death among kids in the US. Nov. 18 is #NationalInjuryPreventionDay, and DOH-Marion wants to help save lives. We ask people to wear green on 11/18 to do that, and to learn more about keeping kids safe @  https://t.co/AeNlkfxUgm.   #BeInjuryFree  https://t.co/33cWt9kd5d

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: It's #DiabetesAwarenessMonth, and a good time to share that DOH-Marion and Marion County Hospital District are jointly hosting a free diabetes education class. The 6-week program starts Jan. 19 at the Fort McCoy public library. For more info, call 352-644-2624 or 352-438-2560  https://t.co/pF9eSQNTzC

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: We can show you how to better protect your most precious cargo by using a car seat properly. From 5:30-7:30 p.m., Nov. 18, DOH-Marion offers a free class for families receiving any type of aid and needing a new car seat. You must register in advance. To do so, call 352-644-2751.  https://t.co/2XCoC9v3sf
